> If you ask us, the pita is the ultimate pocket: You can stuff just about anything in it and if it overflows that means you stuffed it right. These pita pockets are just one example. You'll fill the pita with a fresh cucumber and tomato salad, a swipe of hummus, a creamy and tangy dill dressing, feta, and as much hot sauce as your taste buds desire. When you're ready to eat, don't let any dripping sauce or salad go to waste—that's what your fingers are for!

Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @Cucumber{1%unit} lengthwise; slice into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @Dill{1/4%ounce}. Halve @Lemon{1%unit}. Halve @Pita Bread{2%unit}.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together cucumber, tomatoes, @Pepitas{1/2%ounce}, half the dill, a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season generously with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{3%tablespoon}, remaining dill, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Wrap pitas in damp #paper towels{} and place on a #plate{}. Microwave until warm, ~{20%seconds}. Fill each pita with a bit of @Hummus{1/2%cup}, veggie salad, dill sauce, @Feta Cheese{1%cup}, and @Hot Sauce{2%teaspoon} to taste. Serve.